{"/service/ndnp/txdn/batch_txdn_crane_ver01/data/sn86089568/00517176564/1937091501/0814.xml":{"full_text":"Japan\u2019s Riposte To\nU. S. Presure\nBy UPTON CLOSE\nThis is the eighth of a series of articles by the bril\nliant radio news interpreter and America\u2019s foremost\nauthority on Pacific affairs, who two years ago indicated\nin his book \u201cChallenge\u201d the present bloody develop\nments, and here tells us what to expect next. Author of\n\u201cRevolt of Asia,\u201d \u201cEminent Asians,\u201d \u201cOutline History\nof China.\u201d\no e e\nEngland sends a stiff note to Japan over the shooting\nf a British ambassador, but talks softly to Italy over the\nhooting up of British shipping. Russia sends an angry\note to Italy over sinking of tankers supplying the Spanish\novernment but temporizes with Japan over the sinking of\nlg_yiet gun bo_gts on the Amur. Such is medern diplomacy.\nThese note-sendings are all done|-\nfor \u201cstrategic\u201d reasons\u2014for their ef\nfect upon third parties. They are|\nattempts to invole outside elements\nin rescue. The British note to Japan,\nif intended to impress Japan, would\nnot have emphasized the shooting of\nnon-combatan in which Britain|\nherself has &l\ufb02d frequently and\nrecently. It would have stressed in\nstead the insult to imperial \u2018majesty,\nto which the Emperor-worshiping\nJapanese must have responded. But\nthe British foreign office was out to\nimpress the United States, not Japan.\nThe note was phrased with a view\nto the greatest propaganda value to\nAmerican newspaper readers. Amer\nicans are more affected by atrocities\nto non-combatants than by insults to\nmajesty.\nThe same indirect idea lay behind\nRussia\u2019s note to Italy. There is small\ndanger of Russia and Italy engaging\nin direct warfare. But Britain is put\non the spot. She must now choose\nbetween her professed new love for\nItaly and support of anti-piracy on\nthe high seas. Further, what is done\nabout illegal seizure and sinking of\nshipping on the Mediterranean sets\nthe precedent for the West Pacific\nOcean. Japan is soon going to be\nseizing or blocking Russian and\nBritish and American shipping there. l\nAt Nuremburg Hitler orates blunt\nly \u201cour agreement with Japan serves\nthe purpose of the civilized world\nagainst an attack which today is be-\ning waged in Spain, but which may\nbe waged tomorrow in the Far East\nor anywhere else.\u201d i\nThe important fact behind all this|\nphenagling is that Stalin is getting\non his feet again in Russia. The\nSoviet power, reorganized after the\npurge, feels a recovery of strength\nand becomes a prime power. Early\nin July following travels in Russia,\nLieut.-Gen. Homma reported to the\nJapanese general staff that: \u201cThe\nRussian army is so disrupted by the\npurge that it can be cons.idered non-\nexistant so far as our plans are con-\ncerned for years to come.\u201d That re-|\nport is proving misleading. l\nYet if the United States stays out,\neconomically and navally, the Jipa-\nnese are confident that they will win\nin record time. The great British\nfleet rouses no fear in them. In up-\nto-date vessels they have more power\nright now than Britain, save for cap-\nital ships, which are meat for sub-|\nmarines. And Japan ranks first in\nsubmarines\u2014 with Italy second! If!\nMussolini can laugh at the British|\nfleet Japan doesn't have to give it\neven a second thought. The great\nBritish Leviathan is caught and held\nbecause of its very hugeness, with/\nGermany at its throat, Italy at its|\nmidriff and Japan astride its|\nscarcely flopping tail. For Bri-i\ntain to attempt the use of force|\nbeyond Singapore is folly. And that\nmeans that if Japan does not get|\nmired down and exhausted in China\nthe Japanese navy is free\u2014if Uncle\nSam does not intervene\u2014to carry out\nthe policy of its fire-eating boss-\nbehind-the-scenes, Admiral Suetsugu,\nwho annouriced two years ago lhlt'\nthe navy's job was to make all the!\nSouth Seas part of Japan's economic\nempire.\nWestern pegples now realize that\nthey paid too little attention to Ja-\npan's preparations. They were too|\nready to listen to idealists who\ntalked of Japan's \u2018liberals\u201d. Whenl\nthey did scan Japan's naval statistics\nthey completely overlooked her un\nofficial fleet\u2014the portion of the Japa\nnese navy which is registered as\n\u201cfishing fleet\u201d conservatiely esti\nmated at 200,000 tons to add to the|\napproximate million tons reported in\nnavy books.\nThese are attended by floating can\nneries which are armed \u2018Mother\nships,\u201d reported to carry in their\nbellies mosquito torpedoers, subs, and\nsupplies ton\u2018the emergency air bases\nestablished \"on the mandated and\nother Jap-controlled islands of the\nWest Pacific. Units of the \u201cfishing\nfleet\u201d do not need to put into port\nbefore going into action. They can\nbe made ready at sea for action.\nUntil we sent a cruiser or two up to\nour Aleutin chain a year ago those\nstrategic islands were entirely in the\npower of this fishing fleet. If the\u2018\nBritish navy can't capture a few\n\u201cpirates\u201d sinking their shipping in\nthe Mediterranean, what luck could\nit expect around the Dutch East In\ndies, the Phillippines and the Archi\npelagoes?\n\u201cIf the British are so weak,\u201d says\none State Department..official, \u201cit\ncertainly does them and us no goodl\nto go about crying their weakness\nbefore the world.\u201d The measure of l\nBritain\u2019s weakness is the measure of\nour dilemma.\nFor Japan fears only one thing\nnow: the use of the economic and\nnaval strength of the United States\nagainst her. The present government\nWAKE UP YOUR\nLIVER BILE-\nMmk and the world lookspank\n_ iMxntirao are only makeshifts. A mere\nbawal taevaaant doesn\u2019t get at the eaas*. it\nUka those good. old Carter'. Little Liver\nPills to get theae two pounds of bile flowing\nfreely and make you feel \"up and up\". Harm-\nMa, gentle. yet amazing in making bile flow\nfrsslv. Ask for Carter's Little Liver Pill* hr\nMM Wabinaaly rafuae anything etoe. M*\nof Japan still feels that inlernauonall\ncredit is necessary to win the war. It\u2018\nthe United States should refuse to\ntake any more\u201d Japanese gold agai.nstl\ndollars, or if we should embargo\nJapanese silk which gives Japan\nyearly a hundred million dollars of\ncredit in New York, Nippon would\nhave to default on foreign loans and\ndo without imported supplies. But|\nthese actions, besides being an open\ndeparture from neutrality, would\nseriously affect our internal econo-|\nmics and politics. As things are ser.i\nup we can't refuse anybody's gold or\nour whole flat price system goes into\na tangle.\nBut this part of it is up to Unc]e?\n\u2018Sam. The militarists in Japan be-\nlieve they can repudiate debts, re-|\nquisition all industry, eliminate pri\nvate wealth and inaugurate military\nsocialism, and carry on to victory\nwith what they can seize and squeeze\nout of their people. In fact, they\nwant to try it. This is one develop-\nment in Japan that our government\nhas consistently tried to discourage.\nEconomic measures on our part\nwould bring it about immediately.\nNext, logically, we would have to use\nthe navy.\nMore about this amazing, and prob-\nably imminent, scheme within Japan\n\u2014which Hitler has just announced he\ncan duplicate in Germany--tomor-\nTOW.\ng\n9\"\n(McClure Newspaper Syndicate)\nRotary\n(Continued from Page 1)\nand W. A. Radford, while they\nbrought along Rev. Everett Seale of\nBeeville, who favored the Rotarians\nwith several vocal selections, having a\nhighly trained and rich base voice.\nThe meeting was under, the direc\ntion of Bruce Brannon, c?'xairman of\nthe inter-city section, who turned the\ngavel over to \u2018Bill' Foster as chair\nman of the day, and he reminded\nRotarians that he was glad to be\nback in Lareflo, where he had made\nhis home up to-several years ago.\nHe then called upon Everett Seale to\ngive several songs. and in addition to\nleading the Rotarians in group sing\ning. and followed with two solos,\n\u201cWhen de Profundo Sang Low C\u201d\nand encore of \u201cBelieve Me if All\nThese Endearing Young Charms.\u201d\nEugene Tips as speaker of the day\ntook for his subject, \u201cThe Glass In\ndustry of Three' Rivers,\u201d and before\nstarting his talk had Jack Mont\ngomery distribute small glass jars\nmanufactured at Three Rivers to the\ngathering. He told of the glass\nmanufacturing plant at Three Rivers,\nwhich was the first in Texas, and\nnow one was being established in\nHouston. He explained the process\nof glass manufacture and how it had\nbeen mouth blown, but now ma\nchines are employed to do that work.\nGlass is made of high grade silica\nsand, he said, soda ash and lime, and\nthat the big alkali plant at Corpus\nChristi was saving the Three Rivers\nglass. works $80 daily in soda ash\nalone. He then fully explained the\nprocess of molding glass into bottles\nand other glassware and explained\nthe tempering of glass and the neces\nsity of maintaining the proper tem\nperature for he molten glass when\nmolding into shapes. He ssaid the\nglass produced in the Three Rivers\nplant was the best in the world and\nfound ready demand in the markets\nof the cdlintry.\nErnest T. Laubscheh, who returned\na few days ago from a trip to Europe\nbrought back a silk\u2019 flag given by the\nZurich, Switzerland. Rotary Club to\nbe delivered to the Laredo Rotary\nClub, saying each club in Switzer\nland had its own flag and this one\nwas emblematic of the great silk in\ndustry of Zurich. FLaubscher was\nthanked for the flag and a letter of\nthanks will be sent by the officers\nof the Laredo Club to the Zurich\nClub.\nMoved to His Home\nLuis Dalrymple, 16, in Mercy Hos\npital the past 14 days following an\ncperation for the removal of a rup\ntured appendix was sufficiently re\ncovered to be moved to te home of\nhis parents, Mr. and Mrs. A. G. Dal-\nIrymple on Garcia street today. i\nNews Behind\n(Continued From Page\nsly dig at the Des Moines address ini\nhis recent magizine article, assert-|\ning that the G. O. P. in 1936 pro:n-!\nised to emulate F. D. R. but \u201cto do\n;it cheaper.\u201d Prospective G. O. P.\u2019\ncontributors want the Landon-\nHoover controversy settled bcl'ox;e}\nthey open their wallets, and they en- i\ndorse the Palo Alto man's restatement\nof principles for the opposition,\n\u2018Hardly anybody envisages Mr\nHoover as a presidential candidut\n~again. But with 1935's sour and bit\nter memories beginning to blur and\nsoften, they think his voice should\nbe- heard and heeded more than it\nhas been in recent years.\nSEARS HIKES\nEXPENDITURES\nN TEXAS\nA 55 per cent increase in the ex\npenditures of Sears, Roebuck and\nCompany during last yesr was an\nnounced todey by W. C. O'Mara,\nmanager of the local Sears retail store\nThis increase represents a total ex\npenditure of $4,700,822 during 1936,\nMr. O\u2019'Mara learned when.a copy of\nsurvey conducted in connection with\nSear\u2019s 5lst anniversary reached him\nthis morning from the executive of\nfices of the compory A huge anni\nversary sales event starts locally and\nin all Sears stores throughout the\nnation, on Thursday.\nOf the total expenditures $1,816,763\ncovered the cost of manufactured\ngoods purchased from 118 sourees\nlocated in 22 Texas ci\u2018ies and towns,\nthe report stated. This represents a\n183 per cent increzse over 1935,\nOther expenditure classifications\nare as follows. for wages and salaries\nof resident employes, $1,977.941; for\nnewspaper advertising, $376,286, and\nfor rents and .axes $529,827.\n\u201cThere is little doubt that busincss)\nin this state has shown a vast im-\nprovement during \u2018he past two or|\nthree years said Mr. O'Mara, and 1|\nam particularly pleased that the ex-\npenditure figures of my company in\ndicate it has been cn important con\ntributor towards this business revival.\n'*OSCILLATE\nR e o\nCon Mims Jr. is preparing to leave\nfor ,school this coming Sunday. He\nwill attend school up in Arlington.\nMary Lewis parading through the\nhalls of the new high school as if she\nhad no classes.\nArturo Benavides is rccovering}\nvery rapidly from his recent opera\ntion.\n#\u00ab*+Hector Cox is a one hundred\nper_cent Laredo booster, and he is!\nalways in behind every Chamber of\nCommerce movement or civic move\nment for the Betterment of Laredo.\n\u2018Heetor is'a comedian and entertaiper\nwho always goes over big on any\nprogram.\nAnnette Brooks and Rosalie Ko-\nwalski, pep squad leaders, were\nstruttin\u2019 away in the hot sun yester\nday with the band.\nHonore Ligarde is another one who\nis preparing to leave soon for school.\nHe will attend the University of\nTexas.\n*The four stars above indicate ai\nperson of sterling quality who is\nreally worth knowing. f\nHiway l)q-partlm'nt\nPuts Road Signs\nIn Spanish\nTexas Highway Department signs\nalong the highway from the interna\ntional bridge at Laredo to San An\ntonio which are at present in English\nonly and advise the motorist of\ncurves, city limits, railroad crossings,!\nstop, overpass, underpass and other\ninformation of a safety nature, are\nduplicated in the Spanish lanzuage\u2018\nand placed, side by side. 1\nResident Engineer Fred M. Percival\nstated that the decision of the high\ntourists who understand the Spam.sh\u2018\nlangu'ge only, of hazards along tne\nwas for the purpose of informing\u2018\ntourists who understand the Spapnish\nlanguage only of hazards along the\nhighway and to have them posled{\nand contribute to safety in the man\nagement of their conveyances,\nHigh School To\nHold Constitution\nWeek Program\nOO\nThe public is invited fo attend a?\nspecial \u201cConstitution Week\u201d program\nof the Laredo High School to be hcld.\nThursday morning at 10:15 in the\nauditorium of the new high school.j\nPrincipal W. J. Lemoine announced\ntoday. i\nNetzer Gets Bid\nThe J. C. Netzer Co. made the suc\ncessful bid to the commissioners\ncourt Wednesday afternoon to iur-f\nnish two trucks to be used by the\u2018\nroad construction department of the\ncounty.\nThe bid of the Netzer concern to\nfurnish tw\u00e9 G. M. C. trucks at a\naost of $1,600, less $850 for trade-in\non old trucks, making the actual cost\nIio the county $1,250, was accepted.\nThree other bids were submitted, but!\n1; the Netzer bid was the lowest.\nil l JII ri\\'\u2014\\?ic el\nIn the presence of District Judges\nJ. FaMullally and R. D. Wright the\njury wheel of Webb county was\nfilled this morning.\nDeputies from the county assessor\nand collector, county clerk, sheriff\nand district clerk filled the wheel in\nthe presence of the two district\njudges and jurors will now be drawn\ntherefrom as needed. This wheel\nwill provide the jurors for both the\n4%h and 111th District Courts.\nD. A. R. Editor\nWASHINGTON, Sept. 15\u2014(#y\u2014Mrs.\nFrances Parkinson Keyes, author of\nbest seller novels, hecame the editor\n\u2018today of the D. A. R. Magazine, of\nficial publication \u00abf the Daughters of\ntha American Revolntion,\ne e e i L LR\nCORNS\nmove corns Cost but a\ntrifle Sold everywhere.\nDfScholls Zinopads\nTHE LAREDO TIMES, WEDNESDAY, SEPT. 15, 1937\nKen McClure Gets High\nNational Honor Position\nWOAI Newscaster\nIs Honored\nKENDALL B. McCLURE\nLaredo Proud Too\nLaredo Today\nRy TS L gz L L\nWEATHER FORECAST: For 'l\u2018cxasl\n\u2014Partly cloudy tonight and Thurs-|\nday.\nFOR EAST TEXAS: Probably\u201d scate,\ntered showers nezr the coast; cooler in\nthe northwest tonight and cooler in1\nthe northeast and southwest Thurs-\nday.\nFOR WEST TEXAS: Slightly cool-\ner in the north tonight. 1\nMARRIAGE LICENSES: Guy Link\n)\u2018,H(\u00bb&s and Miss Thana Roberts, Isidro\n\u2018Alfaro and Miss Anastacia Duarte,\nAurelio P. Ortega and Miss Celia\n1 Anzares R.\nAUTO REGISTRATIONS: Ruben\n!Garcia' Ford sedan; Alfonso Ochoa,\nFord sedan.\nCITY COUNCIL: Regular semi\nmonthly meeting of the city council\ni will be held Tuesday night beginning\n|a'. 7:30 o'clock, Mayor Albert Martin\npresiding.\nPROBATE COURT: In session at\nall times for the submission of prae~\nbate business, County Judge Justo S.\nPenn presiding.\n49TH DISTRICT COURT: Septem\nber term for Dimmit county con\nj\\'cncrl in Carrizo Springs Sept. 6,\nDistrict Judge J. F. Mullally presid\ning.\nIITH DISTRICT COURT: Scp\ntember term convened Sept. 7, Dis\ntrict Judge R. D. Wright presiding.\nMEXICAN SILVER PESO. Buying\nat 27 40. selling at 27:55'\ni Sy it\nr\no\nA\nI\n\na\nA\nMORE PLEASURE\nr\nf\n\nX\na Xffy\n|g\nsilk-\n4,\nCIGARETTES\nFinest Turkish 0.0 Domestic Tobaccos\nPlenty of the right kinds of mild\nripe home-grown tobaccos plenty of the\nright kinds of aromatic Turkish tobaccos\ncut into long even shreds and firmly rolled in\npure cigarette paper and made full cigarette\nsize for the best smoking\nthat\u2019s what full measure\nmeans to Chesterfield smokers\nand that's nhy Chesterfields give\nyou MORE PLEASURE.\nCop,right 1957, Uggxtt Nyuu ToMCCO CO,\nSR 1\nKen McClure, who thinks Laredo\nis one of the best cities in the world,\nand whom Laredo is always glad to|\nsee ,has been nationally honored.\nMcClure was recently elected pres\nident of the Association of Radio\nNews Editors at the pational conven\ntion in Chicago. T!:is came as 10\nsurprise to Ken's many Laredo\nfriends who have been following him\nin his \u201cNewscasts\u201d over WOAI in|\nSan Antonio a number of years. 1\nKen with his charming wife have|\nbeen in Laredo on several occasions.\nThe last was in February when \\.he\u2018\nannual ball program of the Washing-l\nton\u2019s Birthday Association was broad\ncast with McClure announcing.\ne 1\nYom Kippur\no A A\n(Continued from Page 1)\nlargely attended. Wednesday morn-\ning at 10 o'clock services were again 1\nbegun at Legion Hall, with Rabbi\nWax, pregching the sermon on \u201cThe\nJewish Philosophy of Life,\u201d these\nservices continuing throughout the\nday and until sunset Wednesday\nevening.\nRabbi Wax in his sermon Wednes-\nday morning caid that \u201cthe fll\u2018stl\nfundamental that must mark the\nlife of the Jew is individuality. JIn-\ndividuality not in the selfish sense,\nbut in the sense of the sacredness\nof human life.\u201d\nHe said; \u201chowever, when we look\nabout us we see that in the world\ntoday the trend is contrary to the l\nJewish concept of individuality. In\nall too many places there is no long-\ner a recognition and appreciation\nof the dignity and value of the indi\nvidual life. The tendency today is\nto sacrifice the individual in the\n\u2018name of mob mottoes crying for\nslavish uniformity. This trend has\nbecame a universal movement in the\nlife of nations, with the result that\nour individual human life has lost\nits instrinsic value.\n\u201cThe Jew must be on guard lest\nthe paganistic powers that now run\nrampant destroy his individuality\nand annihilate his personality. Once\nagain the Jew must proclaim the bi\nblical concept of man being created\nin the image of God, which means\nthat human life is divine and human\npersonality God-like.\nThis is the moment when like the\nSpanish refugee of old we must\nexclaim: \u201cIn spite of all powers of\nheaven and earth a Jew I am, and a\nI Jew 1 shall remain.\u201d\n\u201cThe second fundamental of the\nJewish way of life is that of justice\nI and righteousness. 'These are the\nvery soul and substance of Jewish\nideaolgy. Indeed, righteousness was\nthe great message of all the prophets\nfrom Moses to Malichi. Abraham\nwas sent forth \u2018to teach his children\nand his house after him justice and\nteousness! and as the law of\nIsrael is' the law of justice, so is the\nhistory of the Jew a continual battle\nfor right. Judaism regards justice\nas one of the most fudamental prin-{\nciples of social equality. It asserts\nthe right of all. \u2018Justice is God,\u2019 says\nthe Bible, and insists on the vindica-\ntion of everyone's right.\u201d\nContinuing Rabbi Wax said: \u201cSure-\nly, our present conditions, under\nwhich the rich grow richer and the\nmiddle classes are gradually cast\ninto poverty and ruin, require a\nhigher and firmer principle to regu\nlate social progress than philantrophy\ngnd love. The lower classes refuse o\nAMAZINGLY\nWHISKEY\nYou\u2019 11 Go for this\nOld\n\nAi\nmoor\nJ\nSmooth Straight\nWhiskey, for Old\nQuaker 's a Marvel\nof Mellowness.\n\nrpHERE\u2019S-always a \u201cclear I\ntrack\u201d for the mellowed\nsmoothness of old Quaker. I\nAnd never a variation in our I\ntheme song: \u201cThere\u2019s A I\nBarrel Of Quality In Every I\nBottle, But It Doesn\u2019t Take I\nA Barrel Of Money To Buy I\nIt.\u201d Taste this whiskey that I\nmakes people say, \u201cIf it\u2019s old\nQUAKER, it\u2019s 0.K.!\u201d Here\u2019s\nproof that you don\u2019t have to\nbe rich to enjoy rich whiskey.\nr.: O\nJ\nWhiskey\n'll\nI\u2019ve Been Workin' on the Railroad\nrve been drink-in' rich Old Qu.k -er\nOLD QUAKER\nSTRAIGHT BOURBON,! WHISKEY BRAND\n.I}^'\nMd-iow\nI've been drink-m\u2019 smooth\nQuaker\nIt is priced for you and me.\nDon\u2019t youhearthe folksallprat\nThis tasty whisk-ey day by i\nDon\u2019t you hear their voic-es\nlive on the crumbs that fall trm:; the\ntable of the upper ones. Justice is\nthe cry of the age. Let each capital\nist and employer look first to the\u2018\nwell-being of the laborer in his em-\nploy. and we shall have few strikes\nand less insecurity in our commer-i\ncial and industrial life. The world\n\\mu_rt be tebuilt on justice.\u201d l{\nNew Lieutenant\nSecond Lieut. Jack Chapman ar\nrived at Fort McIntosh Wednesday\nmorning for station with the Eighth\nEngineer squadron.\n3\nX5l\nIT MEANS SAVINGS\nSEE THURSDAY\u2019S TIMES","height":"20272","width":"15360"}}
